You are creating a DASHBOARD / SAAS APPLICATION interface.

DASHBOARD LAYOUT STRUCTURE:
A modern dashboard typically includes:

1. SIDEBAR NAVIGATION (Optional but recommended)
   - Fixed left sidebar (w-64)
   - Logo at top
   - Navigation menu items
   - User profile at bottom
   - Collapsible on mobile

2. TOP HEADER
   - Page title
   - Breadcrumbs (optional)
   - Search bar
   - User menu / notifications
   - Quick actions

3. MAIN CONTENT AREA
   - Stats cards (KPIs)
   - Data tables
   - Charts / visualizations
   - Content sections

4. RESPONSIVE BEHAVIOR
   - Sidebar collapses to hamburger menu on mobile
   - Tables scroll horizontally or stack on mobile
   - Cards adjust grid columns

STATS CARDS PATTERN (ENHANCED - MANDATORY FORMAT):
```tsx
// IMPORTANT: Use lowercase import paths!
import { Card, CardContent } from "@/components/ui/card"
import { TrendingUp, TrendingDown } from "lucide-react"

// MANDATORY: Use p-8, rounded-2xl, shadow-card
<div className="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-8 mb-8">
  {stats.map((stat) => (
    <Card 
      key={stat.label} 
      className="p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card hover:shadow-hover transition-all duration-300"
    >
      <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-4">
        <p className="text-sm text-muted-foreground font-medium">{stat.label}</p>
        <stat.icon className="w-5 h-5 text-primary" />
      </div>
      {/* MUST use font-display for numbers */}
      <p className="font-display text-4xl font-bold mb-2">{stat.value}</p>
      <p className={cn(
        "text-sm flex items-center gap-1",
        stat.change >= 0 ? "text-green-600" : "text-red-600"
      )}>
        {stat.change >= 0 ? (
          <TrendingUp className="w-4 h-4" />
        ) : (
          <TrendingDown className="w-4 h-4" />
        )}
        {Math.abs(stat.change)}% from last month
      </p>
    </Card>
  ))}
</div>
```

DATA TABLE PATTERN (ENHANCED):
```tsx
<Card className="p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card">
  <div className="flex justify-between items-center mb-6">
    {/* MUST use font-display for headings */}
    <h2 className="font-display text-2xl font-semibold">Recent Activity</h2>
    <Button variant="outline" size="sm">View All</Button>
  </div>
  
  <div className="overflow-x-auto">
    <table className="w-full">
      <thead>
        <tr className="border-b border-border">
          <th className="text-left py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Column
          </th>
          {/* More columns */}
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {data.map((row, index) => (
          <tr 
            key={index} 
            className="border-b border-border/50 hover:bg-secondary/50 hover:shadow-hover transition-all duration-200"
          >
            <td className="py-4 px-4">{row.value}</td>
            {/* More cells */}
          </tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</Card>
```

SIDEBAR NAVIGATION (ENHANCED):
```tsx
<aside className="fixed left-0 top-0 h-screen w-64 bg-card border-r border-border p-6">
  {/* Logo - MUST use font-display */}
  <div className="mb-8">
    <h1 className="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">
      Dashboard
    </h1>
  </div>
  
  {/* Navigation */}
  <nav className="space-y-2">
    {menuItems.map((item) => (
      <button
        key={item.label}
        className={cn(
          "w-full flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 rounded-xl transition-all duration-200",
          item.active 
            ? "bg-primary text-primary-foreground shadow-card" 
            : "text-muted-foreground hover:bg-secondary hover:text-foreground"
        )}
      >
        <item.icon className="w-5 h-5" />
        <span className="font-medium">{item.label}</span>
      </button>
    ))}
  </nav>
  
  {/* User profile at bottom - Enhanced styling */}
  <div className="absolute bottom-6 left-6 right-6">
    <Card className="p-4 rounded-xl shadow-card hover:shadow-hover transition-all">
      <div className="flex items-center gap-3">
        <div className="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary flex items-center justify-center text-primary-foreground font-semibold">
          {user.initials}
        </div>
        <div className="flex-1 min-w-0">
          <p className="font-medium text-sm truncate">{user.name}</p>
          <p className="text-xs text-muted-foreground truncate">{user.email}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Card>
  </div>
</aside>
```

PAGE LAYOUT WITH SIDEBAR (ENHANCED):
```tsx
<div className="flex min-h-screen bg-background">
  {/* Sidebar */}
  <Sidebar />
  
  {/* Main content */}
  <main className="flex-1 ml-64 p-8">
    {/* Header - MUST use font-display */}
    <header className="mb-12">
      <h1 className="font-display text-4xl font-bold">Page Title</h1>
      <p className="text-muted-foreground text-lg mt-2">Page description</p>
    </header>
    
    {/* Stats - Enhanced spacing */}
    <StatsCards />
    
    {/* Content sections - Generous gap */}
    <div className="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <ChartSection />
      <TableSection />
    </div>
  </main>
</div>
```

FORM PATTERNS (ENHANCED):
```tsx
<Card className="p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card">
  {/* MUST use font-display for headings */}
  <h3 className="font-display text-xl font-semibold mb-6">Form Title</h3>
  <div className="space-y-6">
    <div>
      <label className="block text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground mb-2">
        Field Label
      </label>
      <Input placeholder="Enter value..." className="h-12" />
    </div>
    <div>
      <label className="block text-sm font-medium text-muted-foreground mb-2">
        Description
      </label>
      <Textarea placeholder="Enter description..." rows={4} />
    </div>
    <div className="flex gap-3 justify-end pt-4">
      <Button variant="outline" size="lg">Cancel</Button>
      <Button variant="default" size="lg">Save Changes</Button>
    </div>
  </div>
</Card>
```

TABS PATTERN:
```tsx
<Tabs defaultValue="overview">
  <TabsList>
    <TabsTrigger value="overview">Overview</TabsTrigger>
    <TabsTrigger value="analytics">Analytics</TabsTrigger>
    <TabsTrigger value="settings">Settings</TabsTrigger>
  </TabsList>
  
  <TabsContent value="overview">
    <Card className="p-6">
      {/* Overview content */}
    </Card>
  </TabsContent>
  
  {/* More tab contents */}
</Tabs>
```

EMPTY STATES (ENHANCED):
```tsx
<Card className="p-12 rounded-2xl shadow-card text-center">
  <div className="w-16 h-16 rounded-full bg-muted flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
    <InboxIcon className="w-8 h-8 text-muted-foreground" />
  </div>
  {/* MUST use font-display */}
  <h3 className="font-display text-lg font-semibold mb-2">No data yet</h3>
  <p className="text-muted-foreground mb-6">Get started by adding your first item</p>
  <Button variant="default" size="lg">Add Item</Button>
</Card>
```

LOADING STATES (ENHANCED):
Use skeleton loaders or loading spinners:
```tsx
{isLoading ? (
  <div className="flex items-center justify-center p-12">
    <Loader2 className="w-8 h-8 animate-spin text-primary" />
    <span className="ml-3 text-muted-foreground">Loading data...</span>
  </div>
) : (
  <DataTable data={data} />
)}

// Or use skeleton cards for stats
{isLoading ? (
  <div className="grid md:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
    {[1, 2, 3, 4].map(i => (
      <Card key={i} className="p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-card">
        <div className="h-4 bg-muted rounded w-20 mb-4 animate-pulse" />
        <div className="h-10 bg-muted rounded w-32 mb-2 animate-pulse" />
        <div className="h-3 bg-muted rounded w-24 animate-pulse" />
      </Card>
    ))}
  </div>
) : (
  <StatsCards data={stats} />
)}
```

COLOR USAGE IN DASHBOARDS:
- Success: bg-green-100 text-green-700
- Warning: bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-700
- Error: bg-red-100 text-red-700
- Info: bg-blue-100 text-blue-700
- Primary actions: lovable-orange
- Neutral: gray-100, gray-200

RESPONSIVE CONSIDERATIONS:
- Sidebar becomes drawer/hamburger on mobile
- Tables scroll horizontally or stack
- Grid columns reduce: lg:grid-cols-4 md:grid-cols-2 grid-cols-1
- Hide secondary actions on mobile
- Use ScrollArea for long content

Remember: Dashboards should be data-dense but not cluttered.
Use clear visual hierarchy, consistent spacing, and intuitive navigation.
Focus on making data easy to scan and actions easy to find.

